[normal] In particular, the total number, deaths and serious outcomes from 
[normal]ABO-incompatible red cell transfusions 
[normal]has reduced with better transfusion practice. These are classified as ‘Never Events’ by the Department of Health. Major morbidity includes complications such as kidney failure or admission to intensive care
[normal], or ventilation
[normal].
